def: A defect of the eye or of a lens, in consequence of which therays derived from one point are not brought to a single focal point,thus causing imperfect images or indistictness of vision.
Any one of several African monkeys of the genus Cercocebus, asthe sooty mangabey (C. fuliginosus), which is sooty black. [Alsowritten mangaby.]
The water course of a street; a little canal or channel; agutter; also, a puddle. Bp. Hall.
Like, or related to, the genus Sabella.-- Sa*bel"loid, n.
An order of teleost in which the air bladder has no opening.
An examination into one's own state, conduct, and motives,particularly in regard to religious feelings and duties.
One who furthers. or helps to advance; a promoter. Shak.
One given to the introspective method of examining thephenomena of the soul.
The elongation, or angular distance from the sun; -- saidchiefly of the inferior planets. [R.]
A silicate of zinc, usually occurring massive and of a greenishyellow color, also in reddish crystals (troostite) containingmanganese.
